# Database Migration Standards

## Migration file naming — strictly enforced

```text
{6-digit-sequence}_{action}_{subject}.{up|down}.sql
```

Examples:
- `000001_init_schemas.up.sql`
- `000006_create_users.up.sql`
- `000006_create_users.down.sql`
- `000008_tokens_fk_constraints.up.sql`

Sequence numbers are never reused. If a migration is superseded, a new migration is written (not edit of existing).

## Every migration must have a corresponding .down.sql

```sql
-- 000006_create_users.down.sql
-- Reverse of up.sql; must be safe to run after up.sql
DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS users_updated_at ON ibex_core.users;
DROP POLICY  IF EXISTS users_isolation  ON ibex_core.users;
DROP INDEX   IF EXISTS idx_users_email;
DROP INDEX   IF EXISTS idx_users_org_id;
DROP TABLE   IF EXISTS ibex_core.users;
```

## Expand-contract — never breaking changes in one step

```sql
-- PHASE 1 MIGRATION (backward-compatible addition):
ALTER TABLE ibex_core.agents ADD COLUMN embedding_model TEXT DEFAULT 'all-MiniLM-L6-v2';
-- Code is deployed that reads the new column but also works without it.

-- PHASE 2 MIGRATION (make it required after all code is deployed):
ALTER TABLE ibex_core.agents ALTER COLUMN embedding_model SET NOT NULL;
-- Run only after the Phase 1 code is fully deployed.

-- NEVER do both in one migration on a live system.
```

## Large table index creation — always CONCURRENTLY

```sql
-- WRONG — takes table lock; blocks reads and writes for minutes
CREATE INDEX idx_memories_embedding ON ibex_core.memories USING ivfflat (...);

-- RIGHT — builds without locking (takes longer but zero downtime)
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_memories_embedding
ON ibex_core.memories USING ivfflat (embedding vector_cosine_ops) WITH (lists=100)
WHERE status = 'active' AND deleted_at IS NULL;
```

## FK constraints on populated tables — NOT VALID then VALIDATE

```sql
-- WRONG — full table scan with lock; blocks production
ALTER TABLE ibex_core.tokens
    ADD CONSTRAINT tokens_user_id_fk FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES ibex_core.users(id);

-- RIGHT — add without validation (instant), validate separately (concurrent)
ALTER TABLE ibex_core.tokens
    ADD CONSTRAINT tokens_user_id_fk FOREIGN KEY (user_id)
    REFERENCES ibex_core.users(id) NOT VALID;

ALTER TABLE ibex_core.tokens VALIDATE CONSTRAINT tokens_user_id_fk;
```

## RLS on every new tenant table — enabled by default, fail closed

```sql
-- Every table with org_id must have:
ALTER TABLE ibex_core.{new_table} ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Default: deny all (fail closed)
-- Then add the isolation policy:
CREATE POLICY {new_table}_isolation ON ibex_core.{new_table}
    USING (
        org_id = current_setting('app.current_org_id', true)::UUID
        OR current_setting('app.is_service_account', true)::BOOLEAN = true
    );
```

## Never modify a released migration

A migration that has been applied to any environment (dev, staging, production) is immutable. If you need to change the schema, write a new migration. Modifying applied migrations causes checksum failures in golang-migrate and divergence between environments.
